943
00:50:24,305 --> 00:50:27,673
Craig Kings bury had the
distinction of being the only guy

944
00:50:27,741 --> 00:50:31,041
who was driving under the
influence a team of oxen.

945
00:50:31,362 --> 00:50:35,048
And was loaded and smashed
and driving these cows around.

946
00:50:35,366 --> 00:50:39,462
Just in talking about fishing
and sharking and this and that,

947
00:50:39,853 --> 00:50:42,151
Craig gave me some great lines.

948
00:50:43,107 --> 00:50:45,007
One of the lines was,

949
00:50:45,109 --> 00:50:49,706
"It's not like going out there to
catch bluegills or Tommy cods."

950
00:50:49,797 --> 00:50:51,276
That's Craig's line.

951
00:50:51,382 --> 00:50:53,009
I'll catch this bird for you.

952
00:50:53,117 --> 00:50:55,552
It ain't going to
be easy. Bad fish.

953
00:50:56,437 --> 00:50:57,848
Not like going down to the pond

954
00:50:57,955 --> 00:51:00,606
and chasing bluegills or Tommy cods.

955
00:51:01,809 --> 00:51:04,119
This shark, swallow you whole.

956
00:51:04,612 --> 00:51:08,924
Craig Kings bury, because he played
Ben Gardner, got to have his head

957
00:51:10,034 --> 00:51:12,298
life-cast for the mold

958
00:51:13,337 --> 00:51:16,455
for the severed head
