01:21:12,835 --> 01:21:14,883
He created a camera platform that

1479
01:21:14,953 --> 01:21:17,513
according to the tides or
where you wanted your lens,

1480
01:21:17,589 --> 01:21:19,455
could go just below the surface

1481
01:21:19,525 --> 01:21:21,266
or way above the surface of the water.

1482
01:21:21,377 --> 01:21:24,369
He designed it and
had it built for the movie.

1483
01:21:24,480 --> 01:21:25,480
He also created…

1484
01:21:25,581 --> 01:21:29,279
He had to create the water
box, where you put the camera.

1485
01:21:29,385 --> 01:21:33,629
<i>But he reconfigured the water
box so it was easier to get the focus.</i>

1486
01:21:33,906 --> 01:21:36,125
<i>Your hand in there so you could pull focus</i>

1487
01:21:36,225 --> 01:21:39,126
<i>and still have the water lapping the lens.</i>

1488
01:21:39,228 --> 01:21:41,390
I wanted this movie
to be just at water level,

1489
01:21:41,497 --> 01:21:43,295
the way we are when we're treading water.

1490
01:21:43,399 --> 01:21:46,926
We don't see water three feet off
the water. We see water like this.

1491
01:21:47,019 --> 01:21:48,748
I wanted to get the camera right down

1492
01:21:48,821 --> 01:21:50,767
to where the human point of view

1493
01:21:50,873 --> 01:21:53,399
