1512
01:22:54,203 --> 01:22:55,921
<i>After he saw a demonstration,</i>

1513
01:22:55,988 --> 01:22:58,207
he decided that was the way to do it.

1514
01:22:58,307 --> 01:23:02,084
As a matter of fact, Jaws ended up
being a film shot mostly hand-held.

1515
01:23:02,311 --> 01:23:04,552
One thing I remember
more than anything else

1516
01:23:04,630 --> 01:23:07,474
has nothing to do with
the direction of the picture,

1517
01:23:07,583 --> 01:23:10,951
but has to do with the
incredible contrasts of light.

1518
01:23:13,589 --> 01:23:16,365
You'd see a scene being shot.

1519
01:23:17,743 --> 01:23:21,395
From one angle it's dark,
from the other angle it's light.

1520
01:23:21,497 --> 01:23:24,228
Sunshine, fog.

1521
01:23:27,286 --> 01:23:28,868
I remember thinking to myself,

1522
01:23:28,971 --> 01:23:31,588
"My God! How are you
gonna cut this together?

1523
01:23:31,657 --> 01:23:34,501
"How are you ever gonna get the color

1524
01:23:36,662 --> 01:23:39,245
"to bear anything resembling a match?"

1525
01:23:39,348 --> 01:23:40,975
I'd never seen…

1526
01:23:41,884 --> 01:23:44,979
The islands and oceans have
such incredible differences.

1527
01:23:45,087 --> 01:23:47,886
The ocean is green, it's blue, it's black.

1528
01:23:48,006 --> 01:23:50,418
Sometimes the sky was blue instead of

1529
01:23:50,526 --> 01:23:52,893
the overcast gray look
