1530
01:23:54,363 --> 01:23:57,139
When we got back to LA,
we had to take it into the lab

1531
01:23:57,266 --> 01:23:58,779
and get rid of the blue.

1532
01:23:58,850 --> 01:24:03,003
At the time, the special
effects people didn't really have

1533
01:24:03,105 --> 01:24:07,690
a good way of pulling the blue out
of the film without affecting the faces.

1534
01:24:08,010 --> 01:24:10,695
We wanted the faces to remain untouched.

1535
01:24:10,963 --> 01:24:15,275
And so I decided to try something
that they hadn't tried before,

1536
01:24:15,384 --> 01:24:17,898
which was simply to use
black-and-white film,

1537
01:24:17,970 --> 01:24:19,278
the type they do letters with,

1538
01:24:19,388 --> 01:24:21,334
which is either black or it's white,

1539
01:24:21,406 --> 01:24:25,274
expose it for the very
bright sky with a blue filter,

1540
01:24:25,344 --> 01:24:29,190
and take only the blue of the
sky out and leave the faces alone.

1541
01:24:29,298 --> 01:24:31,096
It happened to work very well,

1542
01:24:31,183 --> 01:24:34,562
and we were able to match
shots very well that way.

